step_data.thought:
I've now explored all four main map layers available for viewing New York City on OpenStreetMap:

1. Standard - The default OpenStreetMap style (currently active)
2. CyclOSM - A cycling-focused map style highlighting bike routes and cycling infrastructure
3. ÖPNVKarte - A public transportation focused map style emphasizing transit routes and stations
4. Humanitarian - A style focused on humanitarian aid/disaster response with clear visibility of infrastructure

In addition to these main layers, I can see there are also some overlay options available for troubleshooting:
- Map Notes (checkbox)
- Map Data (checkbox, currently disabled)
- Public GPS Traces (checkbox)

I've successfully completed the goal of exploring the different map layers available for viewing New York City. I should now report my findings to the user.
